<abstract><t>This document specifies Preferred Path Routing (PPR), an extensible method of providing path based dynamic routing for a number of packet types including IPv4, IPv6 and MPLS.  PPR uses a simple encapsulation to add the path identity to the packet.  PPR can also be used to mitigate the MTU and data plane processing issues that may result from Segment Routing (SR) packet overhead; and also supports further extensions along the paths.</t></abstract>

